MVP-Echo Toolbar - Third-Party Notices

This project stands on the shoulders of an incredible open-source
community. Every tool, library, and model listed here made MVP-Echo
possible. We're grateful to the maintainers, contributors, and
communities behind each one.

========================================================================
SPEECH-TO-TEXT & AI
========================================================================

sherpa-onnx — K2-FSA Project
  License: Apache 2.0
  https://github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx
  The backbone of our local CPU engine. A fast, portable speech-to-text
  runtime that made offline transcription possible without Python or
  heavyweight dependencies. Special thanks to the K2-FSA team for making
  production-grade ASR accessible to everyone.

NVIDIA Parakeet TDT Models — NVIDIA Corporation
  License: CC-BY-4.0
  https://huggingface.co/nvidia/parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v2 (English)
  https://huggingface.co/nvidia/parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v3 (Multilingual)
  https://huggingface.co/nvidia/parakeet-tdt_ctc-110m (CPU)
  The models that deliver 99% accuracy. NVIDIA's decision to release
  these under CC-BY-4.0 made it possible to build a world-class
  transcription tool that anyone can run for free.

ONNX Runtime — Microsoft Corporation
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime
  The inference engine behind our model execution. Fast, reliable,
  and cross-platform. Powers both GPU and CPU transcription paths.

========================================================================
DESKTOP APPLICATION
========================================================================

Electron — Electron Contributors & GitHub
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/electron/electron
  Made it possible to build a native Windows app with web technologies.
  The foundation that lets MVP-Echo live in your system tray.

Chromium — The Chromium Authors
  License: BSD and others
  https://www.chromium.org
  The rendering engine inside Electron. Decades of open-source work
  that we all benefit from every day.

React — Meta Platforms
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/facebook/react
  The UI framework that makes building responsive interfaces feel
  natural. Our entire renderer is built on React.

Vite — Evan You & Vite Contributors
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/vitejs/vite
  Lightning-fast build tool that made our development cycle instant.
  Hot module replacement that just works.

TypeScript — Microsoft Corporation
  License: Apache 2.0
  https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript
  Type safety that caught bugs before they shipped. Made refactoring
  fearless.

Tailwind CSS — Tailwind Labs
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss
  Utility-first CSS that let us build a polished UI without fighting
  stylesheets. Every pixel in MVP-Echo was placed with Tailwind.

PostCSS — Andrey Sitnik & PostCSS Contributors
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/postcss/postcss
  The CSS transformation engine behind Tailwind and Autoprefixer.

Autoprefixer — Andrey Sitnik
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/postcss/autoprefixer
  Cross-browser CSS without thinking about it.

electron-builder — electron-userland
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/electron-userland/electron-builder
  Packages our app into the portable exe that just runs. No installer,
  no registry entries, no mess.

========================================================================
AUDIO & MEDIA
========================================================================

FFmpeg — FFmpeg Project
  License: LGPL v2.1+
  https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg
  https://www.ffmpeg.org/legal.html
  Handles our WebM-to-WAV audio conversion. An absolute workhorse
  that's been powering media processing for over two decades.

  Source code for the bundled version is available at the URL above
  or upon request, per LGPL requirements.

========================================================================
GPU SERVER (mvp-stt-docker)
========================================================================

FastAPI — Sebastian Ramirez
  License: MIT
  https://github.com/tiangolo/fastapi
  The API framework behind our GPU transcription server. Fast to build,
  fast to run, beautifully documented.

Uvicorn — Encode
  License: BSD 3-Clause
  https://github.com/encode/uvicorn
  The ASGI server that keeps our transcription endpoint responsive.

Docker — Docker, Inc.
  License: Apache 2.0
  https://www.docker.com
  Makes deploying the GPU server a single command. Containerization
  that actually simplifies things.

NVIDIA CUDA — NVIDIA Corporation
  https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-toolkit
  The GPU computing platform that makes sub-300ms transcription possible.

Python — Python Software Foundation
  License: PSF License
  https://www.python.org
  Powers the GPU server side. The language that made AI accessible.

NumPy — NumPy Contributors
  License: BSD 3-Clause
  https://github.com/numpy/numpy
  The numerical computing backbone behind our audio processing.

SoundFile — Bastian Bechtold
  License: BSD 3-Clause
  https://github.com/bastibe/python-soundfile
  Clean audio file I/O for the GPU server.

websockets — Aymeric Augustin
  License: BSD 3-Clause
  https://github.com/python-websockets/websockets
  Real-time communication between the bridge and sherpa-onnx server.

Hugging Face Hub — Hugging Face
  License: Apache 2.0
  https://github.com/huggingface/huggingface_hub
  Model distribution that just works. Download, cache, done.

